Installation instructions:

..$svn co http://leopold-loewenheim.uni.lu/svn/repos/Digraph3

cd to the svn or the extracted <Digraph3> directory:

.. /Digraph3$ make docHTML
generates the HTML documentation in the ./doc subdirectory
(hyperlatex needed ..$ apt-get install hyperlatex)

.. /Digraph3$ make docPDF
generates a PDF document in the ./doc subdirectory

.. /Digraph3$ make tests
runs a nose test suite in the ./test directory
(python nose package required  ..$ easy_install nose )

.. /Digraph3$ make verboseTests
runs a verbose (with stdout not captured) nose test suite 

../Digraph3$ make install
installs (with sudo !!) the digraphs module in the current running python environment 

Enjoy !!
R Bisdorff
